d explores how hidden technical governance arrangements will become the constitution of our future.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Mai 2022) 0aComputer security. 0aCyberinfrastructurexSecurity measures. 0aInternet governance. 0aInternet of things. 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / Public Policy / Communication Policy.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020 Englishz978311070471608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020z9783110704518oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Political Science 2020z9783110704594oZDB-23-PLW08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Social Sciences 2020 Englishz978311070472308iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertYale University Press Complete eBook-Package 2020z978311069231040uhttps://doi.org/10.12987/9780300249330?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780300249330423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780300249330/original  a978-3-11-069231-0  Yale University Press Complete eBook-Package 2020b2020  a978-3-11-070471-6  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020 Englishb2020  a978-3-11-070472-3  EBOOK PACKAGE Social Sciences 2020 Englishb2020  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-DGGb2020  aZDB-23-PLWb2020